OL,3,CUnearthing the past: How a daughter's
OL,4,Cdevotion exposed her mother's murder
OL,6,FKatarzyna cherishes the few mementoes
OL,7,Fshe has of her mother, and shows me
OL,8,Fone in particular which is especially
OL,9,Fprecious. Mounted in a small box is a
OL,10,Fsingle ear-ring - the one Izabela
OL,11,Falways wore. It was found with her
OL,12,Fremains in Derby.
OL,14,FFrom the hotel, we make the short walk
OL,15,Fto the cemetery where Izabela is
OL,16,Fburied. On the way, Katarzyna buys
OL,17,Fsome flowers and we take in a
OL,18,Ffavourite spot of her mother's, a
OL,19,Fbridge across the Rega river.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/9
