OL,3,CUnearthing the past: How a daughter's
OL,4,Cdevotion exposed her mother's murder
OL,6,FWe return to the hotel for lunch, and
OL,7,FKatarzyna tells me about her hopes for
OL,8,Fthe future, now she finally has
OL,9,Fclosure over her mother's death and
OL,10,Fthe woman responsible has been
OL,11,Fpunished.
OL,13,FShe's a trained masseuse and has
OL,14,Fdreams of setting up her own business
OL,15,Fone day. She undoubtedly has the drive
OL,16,Fand determination to make those dreams
OL,17,Fcome true.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/9
